THIRD-PARTY LICENSES AND ATTRIBUTIONS

This toolkit incorporates code and algorithms from the following sources.
Please refer to the original repositories for their respective licenses.

1. LPIPS (Perceptual Similarity)
   Source: https://github.com/richzhang/PerceptualSimilarity
   License: BSD-2-Clause
   Citation: Zhang et al., "The Unreasonable Effectiveness of Deep Features
             as a Perceptual Metric" (CVPR 2018)

2. pytorch-fid / SIFID
   Source: https://github.com/mseitzer/pytorch-fid
   License: Apache License 2.0
   Copyright 2018 Institute of Bioinformatics, JKU Linz

3. ArtFID
   Source: https://github.com/matthias-wright/art-fid
   License: MIT
   Citation: Wright & Ommer, "ArtFID: Quantitative Evaluation of Neural
             Style Transfer" (GCPR 2022)

4. HistoGAN (RGB-uv Histogram)
   Source: https://github.com/mahmoudnafifi/HistoGAN
   Copyright 2021 Mahmoud Afifi
   Citation: Afifi et al., "HistoGAN: Controlling Colors of GAN-Generated
             and Real Images via Color Histograms" (CVPR 2021)

5. MambaST / StyleID / AttenST (Evaluation Framework)
   Source: https://github.com/FilippoBotti/MambaST
           https://github.com/jiwoogit/StyleID
           https://github.com/HuanBor/AttenST
   License: MIT (StyleID), others unspecified
   Citations: See README.md for full bibliography

6. ReCoNet-PyTorch (Warping/Temporal Utilities)
   Source: https://github.com/safwankdb/ReCoNet-PyTorch
   Citation: Gao et al., "ReCoNet: Real-time Coherent Video Style Transfer
             Network" (ACCV 2018)

7. MiDaS (Depth Estimation)
   Source: https://github.com/intel-isl/MiDaS
   License: MIT

8. AdaIN-style / pytorch-AdaIN
   Source: https://github.com/xunhuang1995/AdaIN-style
           https://github.com/naoto0804/pytorch-AdaIN
   License: MIT
   Citation: Huang & Belongie, "Arbitrary Style Transfer in Real-time with
             Adaptive Instance Normalization" (ICCV 2017)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If you use this toolkit in academic work, please cite the relevant papers
listed in the README.md and the original papers for the metrics you use.

